Description: CVE-2026-34355 - Fix heap buffer overflow in mod_proxy_html
 A buffer overflow in mod_proxy_html in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.67 and earlier
 allows an attack by an untrusted backend. The fix simplifies the module to
 use the ap_varbuf API: replaces buf/offset/avail in saxctxt with
 struct ap_varbuf vb, and dump_content uses ap_varbuf_regsub for regex
 substitutions, avoiding manual buffer resizing with preserve/memmove/memcpy
 that could overflow.
 .
 Backport of upstream r1934977 (2.4.x branch) / r1934975 (trunk),
 which shipped in Apache HTTPD 2.4.68.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/d62fc375281486c6036b007ac349b25d4e6edb4a
Author: Joe Orton <jorton@apache.org>
Bug: https://httpd.apache.org/security/vulnerabilities_24.html
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/1139340
Last-Update: 2026-06-10
