Description: Fix CVE-2026-44185 OCSP request buffer pointer advance bug
 In modules/ssl/ssl_util_ocsp.c send_request(), the write-buffer pointer
 wbuf was being advanced by the requested byte count (remain) rather than
 the number of bytes actually sent (wlen returned by apr_socket_send).
 When apr_socket_send performs a short write, this causes the next loop
 iteration to skip ahead past unsent data and re-read past the end of the
 buffer, sending corrupted OCSP request data to the responder.
 Increment wbuf by wlen (bytes actually sent) instead of remain.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/32b7e2e66477020ba75b78ab43fb8890ec292ad2
Author: Joe Orton <jorton@apache.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-10
---
--- a/modules/ssl/ssl_util_ocsp.c
+++ b/modules/ssl/ssl_util_ocsp.c
