Description: CVE-2026-34356 - ap_proxy_cookie_reverse_map: fix dup path/domain
 Heap-based buffer overflow in ap_proxy_cookie_reverse_map() in
 modules/proxy/proxy_util.c. When ProxyPassReverseCookieDomain or
 ProxyPassReverseCookiePath is configured and a malicious backend
 returns a Set-Cookie header containing duplicate path= or domain=
 attributes, stale newpath/newdomain pointers and pdiff/ddiff length
 deltas carry over from earlier iterations, causing an out-of-bounds
 write during cookie rewriting.
 .
 Per RFC 6265 sections 5.3 4) and 5.3 7) only the last path= and
 domain= attributes are meaningful, so reset newpath/pdiff and
 newdomain/ddiff each time a new attribute is seen.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/403269396d24404e2576a9b20f96cd0b10574048
Author: Eric Covener <covener@apache.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-10
---
--- a/modules/proxy/proxy_util.c
+++ b/modules/proxy/proxy_util.c
@@ -1036,6 +1036,12 @@ PROXY_DECLARE(const char *) ap_proxy_cookie_reverse_map(request_rec *r,
             poffs = pathp - tmpstr_orig;
             l1 = strlen(pathp);
             pathe = str + poffs + l1;
+            /*
+             * RFC 6265 § 5.3 7): Only the last path= should be meaningful
+             * so reset anything previously found.
+             */
+            newpath = NULL;
+            pdiff = 0;
             if (conf->interpolate_env == 1) {
                 ent = (struct proxy_alias *)rconf->cookie_paths->elts;
             }
@@ -1056,6 +1062,12 @@ PROXY_DECLARE(const char *) ap_proxy_cookie_reverse_map(request_rec *r,
             doffs = domainp - tmpstr_orig;
             l1 = strlen(domainp);
             domaine = str + doffs + l1;
+            /*
+             * RFC 6265 § 5.3 4): Only the last domain= should be meaningful
+             * so reset anything previously found.
+             */
+            newdomain = NULL;
+            ddiff = 0;
             if (conf->interpolate_env == 1) {
                 ent = (struct proxy_alias *)rconf->cookie_domains->elts;
             }
Description: CVE-2026-44186 - mod_proxy_ftp: fix infinite loop on Retry-After
 The Retry-After parser in mod_proxy_ftp scans for a digit preceded by
 whitespace inside the FTP server response. When no such digit is found,
 the body of the while loop never advances secs_str, causing the worker
 thread to spin forever (denial of service). This patch wraps the loop
 body in braces and adds the missing secs_str++ increment so the loop
 terminates when the response contains no qualifying digit.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/414de374a06549b2c6710cbcff81c3821379f75c
Author: Eric Covener <covener@apache.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-10
